reviews.review_text: Exceptional all around! Another great recording with a Charlie Miller touch. I really dig the Aucostic Aiko and China Doll, but really there is scarcely a dull moment. The band and the audience provide top notch performance and interaction. The recording balances all of this out wonderfully. There were a number of acoustic/electric shows in 1980, including I believe about 15 at the Warfield in SF and a week later another 10 at Radio City Music Hall, NYC. That is why this show as taken so long to get a review, it has been buried under all of those other wonderful recordings. Personally, I just wanted 1 from each venue and this is the one I chose from NYC. I suggest downloading this one ASAP!
